Section 1:
1 L.D. 269
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 ENVIRONMENT AND NATURAL RESOURCES
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 172, L.D. 269, “Resolve, Regarding
10 Legislative Review of Portions of Chapter 375: No Adverse Environmental Effect
11 Standards of the Site Location of Development Act, a Major Substantive Rule of the
12 Department of Environmental Protection”
13 Amend the resolve in section 1 in the 5th line (page 1, line 18 in L.D.) by striking out
14 the following: "authorized." and inserting the following: 'authorized only if the following
15 changes are made:'
16 Amend the resolve in section 1 by inserting after the first paragraph the following:
17 '1. The rule must be amended to remove Section 15-A(B)(1)(b); and
18 2. The rule must be amended to remove Section 15-A(B)(3)(e).
19 The rule may be amended as necessary to incorporate, through formatting and
20 numbering and other technical, nonsubstantive revisions, the changes described in
21 subsections 1 and 2.'
22 Amend the resolve by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
23 section number to read consecutively.
24 SUMMARY
2255 This amendment amends the resolve to authorize final adoption of Chapter 375: No
2266 Adverse Environmental Effect Standards of the Site Location of Development Act, a major
2277 substantive rule of the Department of Environmental Protection that was submitted for
2288 legislative review, only if certain specified changes are made to that rule prior to final
2299 adoption.
Page 1 - 132LR1493(03)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
